ovements are usually majesty and vigour. It also depends on the style & tempo of music, which punctuated by various lyrical song recitations. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ich.unesco.org/en/lists|title=UNESCO - Cheoyongmu|website=ich.unesco.org|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> The dance is always perform by five dancers, its costumes and mask are noteworthy. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://english.cha.go.kr/cop/bbs/selectBoardArticle.do?ctgryLrcls=CTGRY210&nttId=58142&bbsId=BBSMSTR_1205&uniq=0&mn=EN_03_02|title=Intangible Cultural Heritage of Humanity {{!}} Cultural Heritage Administration|website=english.cha.go.kr|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Korean dance]]\n*[[Korean mask]]\n*[[Korean mythology]]\n*[[Samguk Yusa]]\n*[[Akhak Gwebeom]]\n*[[Korean shamanism]]\n*[[Important Intangible Cultural Properties of Korea]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n* {{cite book|title=Perspectives on Korean Dance |author=Judy Van Zile |url=https://archive.org/details/perspectivesonko0000vanz |url-access=registration |quote=081956494X. |isbn=0-8195-6494-X |year=2001 |publisher=[[Wesleyan University]] Press |pages=65p-109p |work=Ch'\u014fyongmu}}\n* {{cite journal|title=The performances and the folklore related to the Cheoyongmu played in each region (\ucc98\uc6a9\ubb34\uc758 \uc131\ub9bd\uacfc \uac01 \uc9c0\ubc29\uc758 \uad00\ub828  \ubbfc\uc18d\uc5f0\ud76c \ubc0f \ubbfc\uc18d)|author=Jeon Kyung-Wook (\uc804\uacbd\uc6b1) |date=December 2006|url=http://www.dbpia.co.kr/view/ar_view.asp?arid=905773|language=Korean |publisher=Korean Folk Studies (\u97d3\u570b\u6c11\u4fd7\u5b78) |issue=44}}\n* {{cite book|title=Cheoyongmu, Important Intangible Cultural Property No.39 (\ucc98\uc6a9\ubb34, \uc911\uc694 \ubb34\ud615 \ubb38\ud654\uc7ac \uc81c 39\ud638)|author=Lee Hueng-Goo (\uc774\ud765\uad6c)|publisher=Hwasan Publishing (\ud654\uc0b0\ubb38\ud654\uc0ac)|language=Korean|year=2000 |isbn=89-86277-36-0}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://210.95.200.119/100_ncktpa/400_Book/300003/057.