a-stub}}\n{{Dance-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Linda Evans L", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:expired website link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cheoyongmu"}
{"title_page": "2017 National Invitational Softball Championship", "text_new": "{{short description|College softball tournament}}\n{{Infobox NCAA Tournament yearly\n| custom_title = 2017 National Invitational Softball Championship\n| year  =  2017\n| division  = \n| sport  =  Softball\n| image  =  \n| image_size  =  \n| caption  =  \n| season  =  2017 NCAA Division I softball season\n| teams  = 26\n| format = Double Elimination\n| finals_site  = Kamphuis Field<br />at Liberty Softball Stadium, [[Lynchburg, VA]]\n| champions  = [[Liberty Lady Flames softball|Liberty]]\n| title_count  = 1st\n| runner_up  = [[Lamar Lady Cardinals softball|Lamar]]\n| game_count  = 1st\n| semifinal1  =  \n| semifinal2  =  \n| coach  = [[Dot Richardson]]\n| coach_count  = 1st\n| MVP_label  = MVP\n| MVP  = Tori Zavodny\n| MVP_team  = Liberty\n| attendance  =  \n| television  =  \n| radio  =  \n| prev  = \n| tournament_link  = National Invitational Softball Championship\n| next  = [[2018 National Invitational Softball Championship|2018]]\n}}\nThe '''2017 National Invitational Softball Championship''' (NISC) began on May 16, 2017 and concluded on May 24. The Liberty University [[Liberty Flames and Lady Flames|Lady Flames]] defeated the Lamar University [[Lamar Cardinals and Lady Cardinals|Lady Cardinals]] in a controversial rain-shortened two-game final on Liberty's home.field in [[Lynchburg, Virginia]].\n\n\n==Tournament play and team selection==\n\nThe NISC tournament is designed to feature forty-eight teams in eight six-team regional tournaments with the regional champions advancing to a National Finals tournament. The regionals and the Finals are [[Double-elimination tournament|double-elimination]] competitions.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.womensnisc.com/event-details.html |title=Event Details |publisher=National Invitational Softball Championship/Triple Crown Sports. |accessdate=November 26, 2017 }}</ref>\n\nFor the inaugural tournament, only fifteen of the thirty-two NCAA conferences sent an automatic qualifier (AQ). Seven schools having non-losing records and [[Rating percentage index|RPIs]] in the top 100 entered the tournament with \"National RPI\" bids. Four other teams with non-losing records against challenging schedules were added as \"At-large\" teams. The twenty-six teams were placed in six regional tournaments of four or five teams. The six regional champions advanced to the National Finals at Liberty University, a site that was determined after the regional competitions. <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.flosoftball.com/article/56137-2017-postseason-nisc-tournament-bracket-announced#.WRsueGjyu70 |title=2017 Postseason NISC Tournament Bracket Announced |publisher=flosoftball.com |date=May 15, 2017 |accessdate=November 26, 2017 }}</ref>\n\n==Brackets==\n''Source:''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.womensnisc.com/bracket.html |title=Regional & Championship Brackets |publisher=National Invitational Softball Championship/Triple Crown Sports. |accessdate=November 26, 2017 }}</ref>\n\nThe six regional tournaments were played May 16\u201318, 2017.\n\nThe regional and finals competitions were [[double-elimination tournament]]s.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; text-width:95%;\"\n|-\n!'''NISC''' ||colspan=\"6\"|'''Region''' (\u2020 = host)\n|-\n! '''Place''' \n! '''1''' <br />''Stockton, CA''\n! '''2''' <br />''Ogden, UT''\n! '''3''' <br />''Normal, IL''\n! '''4''' <br />''Beaumont, TX''\n! '''5''' <br />''Atlanta, GA''\n! '''6''' <br />''Lynchburg, VA''\n|-\n|'''1st'''|| '''[[Cal Poly Mustangs softball|Cal Poly Mustangs]]'''|| '''[[Weber State Wildcats softball|Weber State Wildcats]]''' \u2020 || '''[[Illinois State Redbirds softball|Illinois State Redbirds]]''' \u2020 || '''[[Lamar Lady Cardinals softball|Lamar Lady Cardinals]]''' \u2020 || '''[[Kennesaw State Owls softball|Kennesaw State Owls]]'''|| '''[[ Liberty Lady Flames softball|Liberty Lady Flames]]''' \u2020\n|-\n|2nd|| [[Nevada Wolf Pack softball|Nevada Wolf Pack]] || [[Boise State Broncos softball|Boise State Broncos]] || [[Michigan State Spartans softball|Michigan State Spartans]] || [[Louisiana\u2013Monroe Warhawks softball|Louisiana\u2013Monroe Warhawks]] || [[Georgia State Panthers softball|Georgia State Panthers]] \u2020 || [[Ohio Bobcats softball|Ohio Bobcats]]\n|-\n|3rdt|| [[Pacific Tigers softball|Pacific Tigers]] \u2020 || [[Utah State Aggies softball|Utah State Aggies]] || [[Murray State Racers softball|Murray State Racers]] || [[Abilene Christian Wildcats softball|Abilene Christian Wildcats]] || [[WKU Lady Toppers softball|Western Kentucky Lady Toppers]] || [[UNC Wilmington Seahawks softball|UNC Wilmington Seahawks]]\n|-\n|4th|| [[UC Santa Barbara Gauchos softball|UC Santa Barbara Gauchos]] || [[San Diego Toreros softball|San Diego Toreros]] || [[IUPUI Jaguars softball|IUPUI Jaguars]] || [[Texas\u2013Arlington Mavericks softball|Texas\u2013Arlington Mavericks]] || [[Alabama State Lady Hornets softball|Alabama State Lady Hornets]] || [[Iona Gaels softball|Iona Gaels]]  \n|-\n|5th|| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || [[Tennessee\u2013Martin Skyhawks softball|UT Martin Skyhawks]] ||  [[Campbell Lady Camels softball|Campbell Lady Camels]]\n|}\n\nThe inaugural National Invitational Softball Championship finals were played May 21\u201324, 2017 at [[Liberty University]] in [[ Lynchburg, Virginia]]. Teams were [[Seed (sports)|seeded]] by their RPIs.\n{{6Team2ElimByesBracket \n\n| RD1-seed1= 5\n| RD1-team1=  '''Weber State'''\n| RD1-score1=  '''3'''\n| RD1-seed2=  4\n| RD1-team2=  Liberty\n| RD1-score2=  2\n\n| RD1-seed3= 3\n| RD1-team3= Cal Poly\n| RD1-score3= 6\n| RD1-seed4= 6\n| RD1-team4= '''Lamar'''\n| RD1-score4= '''8'''\n\n| RD1-seed5= 2\n| RD1-team5=  Illinois State\n| RD1-score5= 0\n| RD1-seed6= 4\n| RD1-team6= '''Liberty'''\n| RD1-score6= '''3'''\n\n| RD1-seed7= 5\n| RD1-team7= Weber State\n| RD1-score7= 0\n| RD1-seed8= 3\n| RD1-team8=  '''Cal Poly'''\n| RD1-score8= '''9<sup>(6)</sup>'''\n\n| RD2-seed1= 1\n| RD2-team1= '''Kennesaw State'''\n| RD2-score1= '''4'''\n| RD2-seed2=  5\n| RD2-team2= Weber State\n| RD2-score2= 0\n\n| RD2-seed3= 6\n| RD2-team3= '''Lamar'''\n| RD2-score3= '''2'''\n| RD2-seed4= 2\n| RD2-team4= Illinois State\n| RD2-score4= 1\n\n| RD2-seed5= 4\n| RD2-team5= '''Liberty'''\n| RD2-score5= '''3'''\n| RD2-seed6=  3\n| RD2-team6=  Cal Poly\n| RD2-score6= 0\n\n| RD3-seed1= 1\n| RD3-team1= Kennesaw State\n| RD3-score1= 4\n| RD3-seed2= 6\n| RD3-team2= '''Lamar'''\n| RD3-score2= '''5'''\n\n| RD3-seed3= 1\n| RD3-team3= Kennesaw Stare\n| RD3-score3= 5\n| RD3-seed4= 4\n| RD3-team4=  '''Liberty'''\n| RD3-score4= '''13'''\n\n| RD4-seed1= 6\n| RD4-team1= Lamar\n| RD4-score1a= 5\n| RD4-score1b= 1\n| RD4-seed2= 4\n| RD4-team2= '''Liberty'''\n| RD4-score2a= '''8'''\n| RD4-score2b= '''3'''<sup>(5)#</sup>\n}}\n* # = Game called after 5 innings for inclement weather.\n\n===Championship Game===\n\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #F9F9F9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse;\"\n|- align=center style=\"background: #F2F2F2;\"\n! School\n! Top Batter\n! Stats.\n|-\n| [[Liberty Flames]]\n| Deidra See (DP)\n| 1-3  2[[Run batted in|RBI]]s [[Double (baseball)|2B]]\n|-\n| [[Lamar Cardinals]]\n| Kelly Meeuwsen (2B) \n| 1-3  [[Run batted in|RBI]] \n|-\n|}\n\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #F9F9F9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse;\"\n|- align=center style=\"background: #F2F2F2;\"\n! School\n! Pitcher\n! IP || H || R || ER || BB || SO || AB || BF\n|-\n| [[Liberty Flames]]\n| Julie DiMartino (W)\n| 5.0 || 3 || 1 || 1 || 4 || 4 || 20 || 24\n|-\n| [[Lamar Cardinals]]\n| Laura Napoli (L)\n| 3.1 || 5 || 3 || 3 || 2 || 1 || 15 || 18\n|-\n| [[Lamar Cardinals]]\n| Anissa Rodriguez\n| 1.2 || 0 || 0 || 0 || 0 || 2 || 5 || 5\n|}\n\n==Finals controversy==\nThe tournament had been plagued all week by intermittent heavy rains, In the first Liberty\u2013Lamar Finals game, Lamar had a 5\u20134 lead after six innings, but Liberty scored four seventh inning runs on their home field to win 8\u20135. Lamar coach  [[Holly Bruder]] did not want to start the decisive game because of the threatening weather, but tournament director Dave King opted to have the game played, since it was the last day that had been scheduled for the tournament. In the second Finals game, Lamar scored four runs in the top half of the sixth inning to take a 5\u20133 lead. With two outs in the bottom of the inning, the rains resumed, soaking the field and making it unplayable. Under NCAA rules, in such a situation, the score reverts to the end of the last completed inning. Lamar's four runs were negated, and Liberty was declared the winner of the deciding game, 3\u20131, giving the Flames the inaugural NISC tournament.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://wset.com/sports/local-college-sports/liberty-softball-claims-nisc-title-in-rain-shortened-finale-3-1|title=Liberty Softball claims NISC title in rain-shortened finale, 3-1|last=Walls|first=Dave|work=WSET|access-date=2017-07-09|language=en-US}}</ref> The decision to call the game was made only nineteen minutes after the rains hit, despite the fact that a games on the previous day had been delayed for an hour in one case and four and a half hours in another. As soon as the decision was announced, softball fans around the country and officials of Lamar's [[Southland Conference]] were irate. \"Nobody foresaw this situation would happen,\" King said. \"You can blame me for this.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.beaumontenterprise.com/sports/lamar/article/Tournament-director-takes-blame-for-Lamar-11172123.php |title=Tournament director takes blame for Lamar softball's NISC title game loss |publisher=Beaumont Enterprise/Hearst Newspapers |date=May 25, 2017 |accessdate=May 25, 2017 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://deadspin.com/controversial-rainout-decision-erases-softball-teams-le-1795531687 |title=Controversial Rainout Decision Erases Softball Team's Lead, Costs Them Championship |publisher=deadspin.com |date=May 25, 2017 |accessdate=November 26, 2017 }}</ref>\n\n==2017 NISC All-Tournament Team==\n''Source ='' <ref>{{cite web |url=https://nfca.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=7441:liberty-claims-inaugural-nisc-championship&catid=109&Itemid=149 |title=LIBERTY CLAIMS INAUGURAL NISC CHAMPIONSHIP |publisher=National Fastpitch Coaches Association |date=May 25, 2017 |accessdate=November 26, 2017 }}</ref>\n\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n'''Cal Poly'''\n*Sierra Hyland\n*Crimson Kaiser\n*Chelsea Convissar\n \n'''Illinois State'''\n*Allison Spence\n*Sarah Finck\n*Riley Strandgard\n \n'''Kennesaw State'''\n*Alley Cutting\n*Courtney Sutter\n*Noelle Winkles\n \n'''Lamar'''\n*Ciara Luna\n*Ashley McDowell\n*Brynn Baca\n \n'''Liberty'''\n*Kenzie Friesen\n*Amber Bishop\n*Tori Zavodny - ''Tournament MVP''\n \n'''Weber State'''\n*Kirtlyn Bohling\n*Takesha Saltern\n*KyRae Kogianes\n}}\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n==See also==\n*[[National Invitational Softball Championship]]\n*[[NCAA Division I Softball Championship]]\n==External links==\n* [http://www.womensnisc.com/ NISC website]\n\n{{National Invitational Softball Championship}}\n{{2017 NCAA Division I softball tournament navbox}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2017 National Invitational Softball Championship}}\n[[Category:2017 NCAA Division I softball season|Tournament]]\n[[Category:National Invitational Softball Championship]]\n[[Category:2017 in sports in Virginia]]\n[[Category:2017 in women's softball]]\n[[Category:2017 in American women's sport]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|College softball tournament}}\n{{Infobox NCAA Tournament yearly\n| custom_title = 2017 National Invitational Softball Championship\n| year  =  2017\n| division  = \n| sport  =  Softball\n| image  =  \n| image_size  =  \n| caption  =  \n| season  =  2017 NCAA Division I softball season\n| teams  = 26\n| format = Double Elimination\n| finals_site  = Kamphuis Field<br>at Liberty Softball Stadium, [[Lynchburg, VA]]\n| champions  = [[Liberty Lady Flames softball|Liberty]]\n| title_count  = 1st\n| runner_up  = [[Lamar Lady Cardinals softball|Lamar]]\n| game_count  = 1st\n| semifinal1  =  \n| semifinal2  =  \n| coach  = [[Dot Richardson]]\n| coach_count  = 1st\n| MVP_label  = MVP\n| MVP  = Tori Zavodny\n| MVP_team  = Liberty\n| attendance  =  \n| television  =  \n| radio  =  \n| prev  = \n| tournament_link  = National Invitational Softball Championship\n| next  = [[2018 National Invitational Softball Championship|2018]]\n}}\nThe '''2017 National Invitational Softball Championship''' (NISC) began on May 16, 2017 and concluded on May 24. The Liberty University [[Liberty Flames and Lady Flames|Lady Flames]] defeated the Lamar University [[Lamar Cardinals and Lady Cardinals|Lady Cardinals]] in a controversial rain-shortened two-game final on Liberty's home.field in [[Lynchburg, Virginia]].\n\n\n==Tournament play and team selection==\n\nThe NISC tournament is designed to feature forty-eight teams in eight six-team regional tournaments with the regional champions advancing to a National Finals tournament. The regionals and the Finals are [[Double-elimination tournament|double-elimination]] competitions.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.womensnisc.com/event-details.html |title=Event Details |publisher=National Invitational Softball Championship/Triple Crown Sports. |accessdate=November 26, 2017 }}</ref>\n\nFor the inaugural tournament, only fifteen of the thirty-two NCAA conferences sent an automatic qualifier (AQ). Seven schools having non-losing records and [[Rating percentage index|RPIs]] in the top 100 entered the tournament with \"National RPI\" bids. Four other teams with non-losing records against challenging schedules were added as \"At-large\" teams. The twenty-six teams were placed in six regional tournaments of four or five teams. The six regional champions advanced to the National Finals at Liberty University, a site that was determined after the regional competitions. <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.flosoftball.com/article/56137-2017-postseason-nisc-tournament-bracket-announced#.WRsueGjyu70 |title=2017 Postseason NISC Tournament Bracket Announced |publisher=flosoftball.com |date=May 15, 2017 |accessdate=November 26, 2017 }}</ref>\n\n==Brackets==\n''Source= <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.womensnisc.com/bracket.html |title=Regional & Championship Brackets |publisher=National Invitational Softball Championship/Triple Crown Sports. |accessdate=November 26, 2017 }}</ref>\n\nThe six regional tournaments were played May 16\u201318, 2017.\n\nThe regional and finals competitions were [[double-elimination tournament]]s.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; text-width:95%;\"\n|-\n!'''NISC''' ||colspan=\"6\"|'''Region''' (\u2020 = host)\n|-\n! '''Place''' \n! '''1''' <br>''Stockton, CA''\n! '''2''' <br>''Ogden, UT''\n! '''3''' <br>''Normal, IL''\n! '''4''' <br>''Beaumont, TX''\n! '''5''' <br>''Atlanta, GA''\n! '''6''' <br>''Lynchburg, VA''\n|-\n|'''1st|| '''[[Cal Poly Mustangs softball|Cal Poly Mustangs]] || '''[[Weber State Wildcats softball|Weber State Wildcats]] \u2020 || '''[[Illinois State Redbirds softball|Illinois State Redbirds]] \u2020 || '''[[Lamar Lady Cardinals softball|Lamar Lady Cardinals]] \u2020 || '''[[Kennesaw State Owls softball|Kennesaw State Owls]] || '''[[ Liberty Lady Flames softball|Liberty Lady Flames]] \u2020\n|-\n|2nd|| [[Nevada Wolf Pack softball|Nevada Wolf Pack]] || [[Boise State Broncos softball|Boise State Broncos]] || [[Michigan State Spartans softball|Michigan State Spartans]] || [[Louisiana\u2013Monroe Warhawks softball|Louisiana\u2013Monroe Warhawks]] || [[Georgia State Panthers softball|Georgia State Panthers]] \u2020 || [[Ohio Bobcats softball|Ohio Bobcats]]\n|-\n|3rdt|| [[Pacific Tigers softball|Pacific Tigers]] \u2020 || [[Utah State Aggies softball|Utah State Aggies]] || [[Murray State Racers softball|Murray State Racers]] || [[Abilene Christian Wildcats softball|Abilene Christian Wildcats]] || [[WKU Lady Toppers softball|Western Kentucky Lady Toppers]] || [[UNC Wilmington Seahawks softball|UNC Wilmington Seahawks]]\n|-\n|4th|| [[UC Santa Barbara Gauchos softball|UC Santa Barbara Gauchos]] || [[San Diego Toreros softball|San Diego Toreros]] || [[IUPUI Jaguars softball|IUPUI Jaguars]] || [[Texas\u2013Arlington Mavericks softball|Texas\u2013Arlington Mavericks]] || [[Alabama State Lady Hornets softball|Alabama State Lady Hornets]] || [[Iona Gaels softball|Iona Gaels]]  \n|-\n|5th|| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || [[Tennessee\u2013Martin Skyhawks softball|UT Martin Skyhawks]] ||  [[Campbell Lady Camels softball|Campbell Lady Camels]]\n|}\n\nThe inaugural National Invitational Softball Championship finals were played May 21\u201324, 2017 at [[Liberty University]] in [[ Lynchburg, Virginia]]. Teams were [[Seed (sports)|seeded]] by their RPIs.\n{{6Team2ElimByesBracket \n\n| RD1-seed1= 5\n| RD1-team1=  '''Weber State\n| RD1-score1=  '''3\n| RD1-seed2=  4\n| RD1-team2=  Liberty\n| RD1-score2=  2\n\n| RD1-seed3= 3\n| RD1-team3= Cal Poly\n| RD1-score3= 6\n| RD1-seed4= 6\n| RD1-team4= '''Lamar\n| RD1-score4= '''8\n\n| RD1-seed5= 2\n| RD1-team5=  Illinois State\n| RD1-score5= 0\n| RD1-seed6= 4\n| RD1-team6= '''Liberty\n| RD1-score6= '''3\n\n| RD1-seed7= 5\n| RD1-team7= Weber State\n| RD1-score7= 0\n| RD1-seed8= 3\n| RD1-team8=  '''Cal Poly\n| RD1-score8= '''9<sup>(6)</sup>\n\n| RD2-seed1= 1\n| RD2-team1= '''Kennesaw State\n| RD2-score1= '''4\n| RD2-seed2=  5\n| RD2-team2= Weber State\n| RD2-score2= 0\n\n| RD2-seed3= 6\n| RD2-team3= '''Lamar\n| RD2-score3= '''2\n| RD2-seed4= 2\n| RD2-team4= Illinois State\n| RD2-score4= 1\n\n| RD2-seed5= 4\n| RD2-team5= '''Liberty\n| RD2-score5= '''3\n| RD2-seed6=  3\n| RD2-team6=  Cal Poly\n| RD2-score6= 0\n\n| RD3-seed1= 1\n| RD3-team1= Kennesaw State\n| RD3-score1= 4\n| RD3-seed2= 6\n| RD3-team2= '''Lamar\n| RD3-score2= '''5\n\n| RD3-seed3= 1\n| RD3-team3= Kennesaw Stare\n| RD3-score3= 5\n| RD3-seed4= 4\n| RD3-team4=  '''Liberty\n| RD3-score4= '''13\n\n| RD4-seed1= 6\n| RD4-team1= Lamar\n| RD4-score1a= 5\n| RD4-score1b= 1\n| RD4-seed2= 4\n| RD4-team2= '''Liberty\n| RD4-score2a= '''8\n| RD4-score2b= '''3'''<sup>(5)#</sup>\n}}\n* # = Game called after 5 innings for inclement weather.\n\n===Championship Game===\n\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #F9F9F9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse;\"\n|- align=center style=\"background: #F2F2F2;\"\n! School\n! Top Batter\n! Stats.\n|-\n| [[Liberty Flames]]\n| Deidra See (DP)\n| 1-3  2[[Run batted in|RBI]]s [[Double (baseball)|2B]]\n|-\n| [[Lamar Cardinals]]\n| Kelly Meeuwsen (2B) \n| 1-3  [[Run batted in|RBI]] \n|-\n|}\n\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #F9F9F9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse;\"\n|- align=center style=\"background: #F2F2F2;\"\n! School\n! Pitcher\n! IP || H || R || ER || BB || SO || AB || BF\n|-\n| [[Liberty Flames]]\n| Julie DiMartino (W)\n| 5.0 || 3 || 1 || 1 || 4 || 4 || 20 || 24\n|-\n| [[Lamar Cardinals]]\n| Laura Napoli (L)\n| 3.1 || 5 || 3 || 3 || 2 || 1 || 15 || 18\n|-\n| [[Lamar Cardinals]]\n| Anissa Rodriguez\n| 1.2 || 0 || 0 || 0 || 0 || 2 || 5 || 5\n|}\n\n==Finals controversy==\nThe tournament had been plagued all week by intermittent heavy rains, In the first Liberty\u2013Lamar Finals game, Lamar had a 5\u20134 lead after six innings, but Liberty scored four seventh inning runs on their home field to win 8\u20135. Lamar coach  [[Holly Bruder]] did not want to start the decisive game because of the threatening weather, but tournament director Dave King opted to have the game played, since it was the last day that had been scheduled for the tournament. In the second Finals game, Lamar scored four runs in the top half of the sixth inning to take a 5\u20133 lead. With two outs in the bottom of the inning, the rains resumed, soaking the field and making it unplayable. Under NCAA rules, in such a situation, the score reverts to the end of the last completed inning. Lamar's four runs were negated, and Liberty was declared the winner of the deciding game, 3\u20131, giving the Flames the inaugural NISC tournament.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://wset.com/sports/local-college-sports/liberty-softball-claims-nisc-title-in-rain-shortened-finale-3-1|title=Liberty Softball claims NISC title in rain-shortened finale, 3-1|last=Walls|first=Dave|work=WSET|access-date=2017-07-09|language=en-US}}</ref> The decision to call the game was made only nineteen minutes after the rains hit, despite the fact that a games on the previous day had been delayed for an hour in one case and four and a half hours in another. As soon as the decision was announced, softball fans around the country and officials of Lamar's [[Southland Conference]] were irate. \"Nobody foresaw this situation would happen,\" King said. \"You can blame me for this.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.beaumontenterprise.com/sports/lamar/article/Tournament-director-takes-blame-for-Lamar-11172123.php |title=Tournament director takes blame for Lamar softball's NISC title game loss |publisher=Beaumont Enterprise/Hearst Newspapers |date=May 25, 2017 |accessdate=May 25, 2017 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://deadspin.com/controversial-rainout-decision-erases-softball-teams-le-1795531687 |title=Controversial Rainout Decision Erases Softball Team's Lead, Costs Them Championship |publisher=deadspin.com |date=May 25, 2017 |accessdate=November 26, 2017 }}</ref>\n\n==2017 NISC All-Tournament Team==\n''Source ='' <ref>{{cite web |url=https://nfca.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=7441:liberty-claims-inaugural-nisc-championship&catid=109&Itemid=149 |title=LIBERTY CLAIMS INAUGURAL NISC CHAMPIONSHIP |publisher=National Fastpitch Coaches Association |date=May 25, 2017 |accessdate=November 26, 2017 }}</ref>\n\n{